import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    us_states = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    us_states = us_states[us_states['iso_a3'] == 'USA']
    us_states = us_states.merge(data, left_on='name', right_on='state')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15, 10))
    us_states.plot(column='rate', cmap='OrRd', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8')
    ax.axis('off')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across different states?', fontdict={'fontsize': '25', 'fontweight' : '3'})
    sm = plt.cm.ScalarMappable(cmap='OrRd', norm=plt.Normalize(vmin=data['rate'].min(), vmax=data['rate'].max()))
    sm._A = []
    cbar = fig.colorbar(sm)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.style.use('ggplot')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    avg_obesity_rate = data.groupby('state')['rate'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
    ax = avg_obesity_rate.plot(kind='bar', color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    ax.axhline(y=avg_obesity_rate.mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Obesity Rate')
    ax.set_xlabel('State')
    ax.set_ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    ax.set_title('What is the average obesity rate across all states?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['color'] = pd.factorize(data['region'])[0]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['region'], data['rate'], c=data['color'], cmap='viridis')
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    ax.set_title('Is there a correlation between obesity rates and region?')
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['region'].unique(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data.boxplot(column='rate', by='region', ax=plt.gca())
    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates within each region?', wrap=True)
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

    data['population'] = data['id'] * 100000
    plt.scatter(data['population'], data['rate'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Population')
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between obesity rates and population size?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
